# Journal entries

This folder holds journal posts as .mdx files. The schema lives in
src/content.config.ts under the `journal` collection.

Each entry needs frontmatter (title, summary, published) plus an MDX body.
Optional fields: updated, cover (image path), tags, draft.

Example:

    ---
    title: Why I keep ripping out page builders
    summary: A short note on the maintenance cost of WYSIWYG stacks for small orgs.
    published: 2026-04-12
    tags: [process, opinions]
    ---

    Prose goes here in MDX...

Drop a file, rebuild, and it appears at /journal/{filename}/ plus the
/journal index. Posts with `draft: true` are excluded from production
builds.

This .gitkeep file is here so the empty folder commits cleanly; remove
once there are real entries.
